        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 3:07PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 307 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Shopton, or 12 miles west of Union Springs, moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Eastern Montgomery, Tuskegee, Union Springs, Pike Road, Shorter, Pine
Level, Auburn University In Montgomery, Franklin Field, Beans
Crossroads, Shopton, Davisville, Waugh, Liverpool, Hardaway, Mount
Meigs, Sprague, Tysonville, Victoryland, Pinedale, and Warriorstand.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
